yingyinNormal.en: Quite a few? Yes, quite a few.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要多放吗？是的，要多放。

yingyinNormal.en: You see, it's quite firm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看，有点硬。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, she's quite a character.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她可真特别啊。

yingyinNormal.en: That sounds like quite a world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听起来还真像那么回事儿。

yingyinNormal.en: The game was quite a simple one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个游戏很简单。

yingyinNormal.en: It's quite a leap to jump to an A.I.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不可能据此一下子跳到人工智能。

yingyinNormal.en: He paints quite a picture, doesn't he?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他说得很有画面感，不是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And you? I thought it was quite tasty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你呢？我觉得很好吃。

yingyinNormal.en: Doesn't sound quite as poetic, does it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 听起来一点也不浪漫，对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Mr Nugent. You've done quite well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 纽金特先生，你做得挺不错。

yingyinNormal.en: Look at you. Quite the chipper sous-chef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看你，简直就是个快乐的小厨子。

yingyinNormal.en: That's quite a step up from a DUI. It is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可比酒驾严重多了。没错。

yingyinNormal.en: She's got quite an arm there, doesn't she?
yingyinNormal.zh: 她扔的真准啊,不是吗? 是的.

yingyinNormal.en: I can assure you, he's quite safe with me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我向你保证, 他和我在一起会很安全

yingyinNormal.en: You do realize it is quite illegal? Of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道这是违法的吧？当然。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you well, Mr Darcy? Quite well, thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好吗，达西先生？非常好，谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: Ohh, okay. Something didn't quite add up there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，难怪我觉得怪怪的。

yingyinNormal.en: Collateral damage? Yeah, quite a lot, I'm afraid.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还是有附带损害？对，恐怕还很大。

yingyinNormal.en: It's quite windy. Let's play a game to keep warm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 风真大。我们来玩个游戏保持温暖吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, you're quite beautiful. Why, thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道吗？你很漂亮。谢谢夸奖。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Unfortunately, the long-term costs of using simple quantitative metrics to assess researcher merit are likely to be <highlight>quite</highlight> great.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不幸的是，使用简单的定量指标来评估研究人员的价值，其长期成本可能相当大。

examination_example.sentence: He thinks his job as a technician <highlight>quite</highlight> challenging.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他认为他的技术员的工作很有挑战性。

examination_example.sentence: It is <highlight>quite</highlight> possible that the homework helped.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很可能是家庭作业帮了忙。

examination_example.sentence: I've found <highlight>quite</highlight> a few, and—since I started posting them on Twitter—they have been causing <highlight>quite</highlight> a stir.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我发现了不少，而且自从我开始在推特上发布它们以来，它们已经引起了相当大的轰动。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Quite</highlight> a lot, according to a handful of scientists quoted in the News Feature.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据新闻专题中引用的少数科学家的说法，有相当多。

examination_example.sentence: Money may not <highlight>quite</highlight> buy happiness, but people in wealthier countries are generally happier than those in poor ones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 金钱可能并不能完全买到幸福，但富裕国家的人通常比贫穷国家的人更幸福。

word_usage.usage: quite同形容词连用修饰名词时，置于a或an之前，可以说It's quite a small house.或Their house is quite small. 但不说It's a quite small house.。
quite可以修饰形容词和副词，其程度稍强于fairly，但弱于very。
quite 可以表示某事物比预料中更加具备某特点，例如，Nobody here's ever heard of it but it is actually quite common. 这里没有人听说过它，但是它实际上颇为常见。

word_usage.usage: quite作副词，可用于加强语气，意思相当于汉语的“完全，十分”，常与没有比较级的形容词(如correct，unique等)以及表示极度的形容词或副词(如amazing，unbelievable，brilliantly等)连用。
fairly，quite，rather以及pretty的比较：四个词均属于程度副词。fairly一般修饰形容词与副词，表示很一般的程度。 quite一般修饰动词和名词，表示的程度要比fairly深一点。 rather一般修饰动词（尤其是感官动词）和名词，表示的程度比quite要更强烈一点，意为“比预期的还要多一些”。 pretty是非正式用语，修饰形容词与副词，表示的程度与rather相当。

word_usage.usage:
①修饰动词：I don't quite follow you.我没有完全跟上你。
②修饰形容词、分词或副词：She was quite recovered by supper. 到吃晚饭时她已经恢复得不错了。
③修饰介词短语：You are quite behind your age. 你看上去比实际年龄小得多。
④修饰名词：We have quite the same idea. 我们的观点很相同。当名词前有形容词时"，quite多放在冠词之前：quite a good dictionary 一本很好的词典；quite还可以直接修饰带a的名词：She is quite a beauty.她真是个美人。
⑤和表示数量意义的名词连用时，表示“相当大，相当多"：I have quite a family.我的家庭相当大。有时表示“相当成功，不错"等：That is quite a party.晚会相当成功。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: fairly不能用在动词和冠词的前面。后面的名词若有形容词修饰，fairly放在冠词后面。
quite能用在动词和冠词的前面。后面的名词若有形容词修饰，quite放在冠词前面。表示部分否定“不完全是那样”，用not quite。
rather能用在动词和冠词的前面。后面的名词若有形容词修饰，rather放在冠词前后皆可，rather放在冠词前更普遍。rather可与too、比较级连用。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 人们很长时间没见到她了

examination_example.sentence: These days, people have so much pressure, because they're <highlight>quite</highlight> busy studying and working.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，人们压力很大，因为他们忙于学习和工作。

examination_example.sentence: Some of the stories I have heard are <highlight>quite</highlight> surprising.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我听到的一些故事相当令人惊讶。

examination_example.sentence: They were <highlight>quite</highlight> thankful for the waiter's service.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们非常感谢服务员的服务。

examination_example.sentence: I <highlight>quite</highlight> agree with you.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我非常同意你的观点。

examination_example.sentence: Times have changed, but falling asleep in class is still <highlight>quite</highlight> common.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 时代变了，但课堂上睡觉仍然很常见。

examination_example.sentence: Claude Monet's paintings were <highlight>quite</highlight> different from the art styles that were popular in the 1870s France.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 克洛德·莫奈的绘画与19世纪70年代法国流行的艺术风格截然不同。

examination_example.sentence: As my father and I worked together, I began to realize that my dad was <highlight>quite</highlight> an inventor himself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我和父亲一起工作时，我开始意识到我父亲本人可真是个发明家啊。

examination_example.sentence: Encouraging words can go <highlight>quite</highlight> a long way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 鼓励的话会有很大帮助。

examination_example.sentence: The ability to transfer (转移) the written tasks to a computer makes it <highlight>quite</highlight> an environmentally friendly invention.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 将书面任务转移到计算机的能力使其成为一项相当环保的发明。

sense_info_list.zh: (quite a few/ quite some)相当数量的

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Quite</highlight> a few American people love Chinese food very much.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相当多的美国人非常喜欢中国菜。

examination_example.sentence: Took <highlight>quite</highlight> a few photos.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拍了不少照片。

examination_example.sentence: They waited for <highlight>quite</highlight> some time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们等了很长时间。
